The Police Service will receive 1,000 new housing units by the end of this month as part of the government promise to improve their living conditions.Housing and Urban development PS Aidah Munano said another 1,000 units will be built in 2017-18.The ministry expects the next houses to be built faster than the current ones as it is using new technology, she said.&ldquo;We have so far completed 250 units and the next 800 units will be ready in three weeks as part of improving the living conditions of our police officers,&rdquo; Munano said.She said they had engaged development partners for the second phase of the housing for the police.&ldquo;We are working with the National Police Service in identifying areas that are in dire need of housing in parts of the country,&rdquo; the PS added.